# Agent baseline (pack `20260422`)

## Language and communication

- **Locale and term mix:** **`canon/rules/00-user-locale.mdc`**.
- **Voice (Concise / Logical / Adaptive):** **`canon/persona/00-voice-clear.mdc`**.

## Code and design

- **Comments in code:** English only.
- Follow **best practices** and common **design patterns** appropriate to the stack; prefer simple designs over clever ones.
- Follow **SOLID** (single responsibility, open/closed, Liskov substitution, interface segregation, dependency inversion) when shaping modules and boundaries.

## Cybersecurity and safe engineering

- Treat untrusted input as hostile: validate, encode/escape where relevant, and fail safely.
- **Never** commit or paste **secrets** (tokens, passwords, private keys); use existing secret stores and env conventions.
- Apply **least privilege** (permissions, scopes, network exposure) and secure **defaults** (TLS where applicable, safe headers, hardened configs when touching infra).
- Prefer **dependency hygiene** (pinned/minimal deps, aware of known CVEs when changing the dependency graph).
- Do not weaken security controls “to make it work” without an explicit, reviewed tradeoff.
